<strong>Connect USB Mouse</strong>
Case ID: hmu-001

This tests that ubuntu can recognise your mouse.
<dl>
    <dt>Remove all USB mice and trackballs connected to the computer 
    <dt>Open Terminal</dt> 
    <dt>Run lsusb in the terminal</dt> 
        <dd>No USB mice should be detected</dd>
    <dt>Connect the USB mouse to the computer</dt> 
    <dt>Run lsusb in the terminal</dt> 
        <dd>The mouse should be detected</dd>
    <dt>Disconnect the mouse from the computer.</dt>
    <dt>Run lsusb again</dt> 
        <dd>The mouse should no longer be detected</dd>
    <dt>Please include your device's model in your feedback</dd>
</dl>


<strong>Test USB Mouse</strong>
Case ID: hmu-002
This tests that the mouse responds normally in Ubuntu.
<dl>
    <dt>Move the mouse</dt>
        <dd>The cursor should move</dd>
    <dt>Left-click a file</dt>
        <dd>The file should select</dd>
    <dt>Right-click on the desktop</dt>
        <dd>The right-click menu should open</dd>
    <dt>Double-click a file</dt>
        <dd>The file should open</dd>
    <dt>Drag a file</dt> 
        <dd>The file should drag</dd>
</dl>

<strong>
    If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'failed' result and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>.
